ue ways have helped students in their careers many times, and that is the reason students held him in high regard. Vikas Divyakirti is not only an excellent Teacher and Author but also an excellent student who has cracked His UPSC exam in one go, which tells what a knowledgeable person he is. He is very passionate about his work and the Nation. Vikas sir has actively participated in various debates may they be on some reputed news channels or various colleges. He has been actively involved in various debates related to Indian politics and traditions. Biography and Education Dr. Vikas was born on Sunday 26th December 1976 in the state of Haryana. He belongs to a middle-Class Hindu Family and his caste is Haryanvi. As of now he is around 46 years old and is one of the most successful teachers in India. He belongs to a middle-class and educated family. His father and mother were professors at Delhi University and would teach Hindi Sahitya. As a professional, he is a teacher and most of his income comes from teaching. He is married to DR. Taruna Verma, and they have a son named Swastik Divyakirti. He has always been a man of culture and Land. He was always a bright student and always knew in his head that he had to serve his nation. As a student, he always would be involved in his study. He completed his middle school and high school in Saraswathi Shishu Mandir in Haryana and after completing his high school studies, He decided to do a Bachelor of Art (BA) in History at Delhi University and his BA he decided to do his Master's in art (MA) in Hindi Literature and sociology from Delhi University. He was so studious that he holds a degree in LLB, M.Phil. and even holds a PHD. Though he holds so many qualifications he also received a PG degree in English to Hindi translation from Delhi University. Though he has so many qualifications he appeared for UPSC in 1996 and cleared it in his first attempt and became an IAS officer and was assigned to the ministry of home affairs bu