ation from Delhi University. Though he has so many qualifications he appeared for UPSC in 1996 and cleared it in his first attempt and became an IAS officer and was assigned to the ministry of home affairs but he decided to leave his job and decide to teach the students for UPSC preparation and started his own coaching class, Drishti. Career Vikas cleared the UPSC examination in 1996 after which he was assigned to the Ministry of Home Affairs. He worked in the ministry department for a time and then resigned from his job to educate the students at Delhi University. In 1999, he opened Drishti IAS guiding Classes in Delhi to give simplified coaching for UPSC applicants. Vikas Sir Imposed a unique tutoring style to help the scholars prepare for the UPSC test that would help them in their peroration as well as life as dignified people. He started giving his lectures in Hindi which made it easier for the students to understand the syllabus. Then in 2017, he started his YouTube Channel "Drishti IAS" on which he started guiding students all over Bharat where he would post various content that is helpful for students like study material, various information points, lectures and exam strategies that help students with their preparation. As of 2022, it has more than 8.5 Million Subscribers. Vikas sir is the director of the Drishti IAS Coaching Classes. Vikas Sir is also the editor of the current affairs yearly magazine called the' Drishti Current Affairs. Though he has so many achievements he did not stop there and authored a book dedicated to students of this nation named "Nibandh Drishti." With his vision for the country, he has always been a motivator for a student which they are always looking forward to. He always says if you are not satisfied with your job, you can always work on your dream. More about Drishti Classes Drishti UPSC Coaching Classes is one of the leading coaching classes in India, whose founding director is none other than Dr. Vikas Divyakirti who is one 